<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 17 at 11:37AM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Scattered Heavier Snow Showers Pushing Across the Area...
As of 1130 AM, scattered heavier snow showers near and north of
I-88 were pushing east of the I-39 corridor. As these heavier snow
showers push east through 130 PM, areas affected can expect a
brief burst of snow with sharply reduced visibility and a quick
coating of snow, including on some roads, with elevated and less
traveled roadways the most susceptible. Motorists who will be out
driving should be prepared to encounter snow showers and rapidly
changing visibility. When driving in snow, slow down and increase
following distance.</description>
